cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper deals with the complexity of query answering in uncertain relational databases, which is a topic closely related to database theory and logic. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves techniques from logic and complexity theory, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of Boolean queries, which is a topic in artificial intelligence, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of maximal sets of tuples, which is a topic in discrete mathematics, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category.
